## Don't

- Don't modify the DB schema without updating `phase1_schema.py` first.
- Don't hardcode credentials. Use `.env` / environment variables.
- Don't delete `*-cache/` dirs in `data/sources/` — they store paginated API responses and rebuilding requires a full re-ingest.
- Don't write to `commonweave.db` (the empty file). Use `commonweave_directory.db`.
- Don't copy boilerplate across ingesters. Add helpers to `_common.py` instead.
